.TH LPF-UI 8 "June 2026" "lpf 0.1.0-dev" "lpf Manual"
.SH NAME
lpf\-ui \- serve, build, or test the Bonsai browser UI
.SH SYNOPSIS
lpf ui <serve|build|test>
.SH DESCRIPTION
Serve, build, or test the Bonsai/Bonsai_web browser UI.
The browser UI uses typed OCaml API endpoints and never executes host commands directly.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
\-\-mock
serve UI with mock API responses
.TP
\-\-listen <addr:port>
bind UI server address
.SH EXAMPLES
lpf ui serve \-\-mock
lpf ui serve \-\-listen 127.0.0.1:9443
.SH FILES
/var/lib/lpf/ui\-session
/var/lib/lpf/history
.SH SAFETY NOTES
Bind to localhost by default.
Require plan checksum confirmation for destructive actions.
Keep rollback preimages server\-side.
.SH EXIT STATUS
0 on success.
Non\-zero when validation, planning, or host operations fail.
.SH SEE ALSO
lpf\-apply(8), lpf\-explain(8), lpf\-support\-bundle(8)
